  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Breast cancer is the most frequent cancer in women and is associated with profound
      restrictions of health-related quality of life and psychosocial health. More than
      three-quarters of women with breast cancer suffer from fatigue during cancer treatment. While
      exercise interventions can improve fatigue in breast cancer patients, many patients request
      complementary treatment approaches. Therefore, this study investigates the effects of yoga in
      women with breast cancer compared to aerobic exercise and usual care.

      It is hypothesized that yoga is more effective than usual care and equally effective as
      aerobic exercise.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
